<div class="container container--narrow">
  <h1>Credits</h1>
  <p>
    {{ site.title }} stands on the shoulders of giants. The code below is what
    makes the app possible. If you ever meet one of these maintainers in a
    pub, buy them a pint.
  </p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Project</th><th>Licence</th><th>Used for</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for c in credits %}
      <tr>
        <td><a href="{{ c.url }}" rel="external noopener">{{ c.name }}</a></td>
        <td>{{ c.license }}</td>
        <td>{{ c.purpose }}</td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Inspirations</h2>
  <p>
    iTunes 9, Winamp 5, Foobar2000, Cog, Audirvana, Swinsian, Vox. We took
    notes from all of them. Mostly the good ones.
  </p>

  <h2>The name</h2>
  <p>
    <em>Bòcan</em> is Scottish Gaelic for a sprite or a hobgoblin — a small
    spirit said to live in the hearth. It seemed appropriate for something
    that lives quietly in your menu bar and plays you music.
  </p>

  <h2>People</h2>
  <p>
    Built by <a href="https://github.com/bocan" rel="external noopener">Chris Funderburg</a>
    at <a href="https://cloudcauldron.io" rel="external noopener">Cloud Cauldron</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Full third-party notices</h2>
  <p>
    The complete <code>NOTICES.md</code> with full licence text is included in
    every release and viewable
    <a href="{{ site.repo }}/blob/main/NOTICES.md" rel="external noopener">on GitHub</a>.
  </p>
</div>
